observations.managementAction:
Comply and adhere to the ecological and solid waste management regulations. And as part of the initial actions of the Municipality, the following have been undertaken:
a. The EWSM garbage hauling crew is strictly enforced to wear their personnel protective gear; 
b. The Municipal Mayor called the attention of the EWSM personnel to hasten the construction of the temporary RCA; 
c. The safe closure and rehabilitation plan of existing dumpsite is on-going; 
d. Procurement of lot for the SLF; and 
e. The Municipality is to procure heavy equipment and pay loader to facilitate the proper management of solid wastes gathered.

observations.recommendation:
The Municipal Mayor will direct the Acting General Services Office and the Accounting Office, to:
a. Conduct the annual physical count of all the property, plant and equipment owned by the Municipality to establish the existence and correct the balances of PPE accounts;
b. Prepare promptly the Report on the Physical Count of PPE;
c. Submit religiously the RPCPPE to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year.
d. Create an Appraisal Committee to appraise all properties whose cost cannot be reliably determined due to unavailabili ty of financial records. Require the committee to prepare Appraisal Report and submit it to the Commission on Audit for Technical Review and Inspection.
We also recommended that the Acting GSO and the Municipal Accountant shall completely maintain the prescribed Property Cards and PPELC respectively and reconcile it with the RPCPPE to establish the correct amount of the PPE in the financial statements.

1. Ensure that the essential elements in GAD planning and budgeting are present or strengthened in the Municipality’s GPB;
2. Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that 5% of the total appropriation is earmarked for GAD in accordance with the minimum requirement set by law;
3. Direct the GAD Focal Point System and other personnel concerned to strictly adhere to the provisions of Joint Circular No. 2012-01 so that the formulation, development, submission, implementati on, monitoring, evaluation and accounting of results of the Municipality’s annual GPB and GAD Accomplishme nt Reports will be in order.
